- Install Node.js:
	Follow these instructions: http://www.hostingadvice.com/how-to/install-nodejs-ubuntu-14-04

- Install MySQL:
	sudo apt-get install mysql-server mysql-client

- Create database 'portfolio':
	CREATE DATABASE 'portfolio';

- Install node packages:
	npm install --save
	npm update

- Create environment variables:
        PORTFOLIO_DB_USER
        PORTFOLIO_DB_HOST
        PORTFOLIO_DB_PASSWORD
        PORTFOLIO_DB_NAME
        PORTFOLIO_SESSION_SECRET

- Start server to automatically create sql tables:
	./bin/www

- Shutdown server

- Import sql script(s) into database from './sql' folder
        mysql -u root -p portfolio < ./sql/projects.sql

- [optional] Create an admin user

- Star server again, go to http://localhost:8080, enjoy :)
